notes: Opcode numbers are within-set numbers; do not include form or operand-type bits.
Some mnemonics vary by version (e.g., 1OP 0xF is 'not' in v1–4, 'call_1n' in v5+; 0OP 0x9 is 'pop' in v1–4, 'catch' in v5/6).
EXT 0x0E–0x0F and 0x1E–0xFF are reserved; interpreters should ignore unknown EXT opcodes >= 0x1D per the Standard.
